<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/27410521-ellen"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/27410521-ellen">Ellen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The Buddha was a symbol of the religion that these women brought from Japan with them. When they had to abandon their houses due to wartime measures, <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The Buddha was a symbol of the religion that these women brought from Japan with them. When they had to abandon their houses due to wartime measures, this item was left behind, which in my mind symbolizes that they were forced to become Americanized and physically leave behind their heritage in order to be accepted in a very difficult time in history for their people. However, this is just my opinion, and there are many other interpretations available.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
