    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2862055737" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2862055737" />
    <a title="Jean-Luke" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9257436-jean-luke"><img alt="Jean-Luke" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642878910p2/9257436.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2862055737?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jean-Luke" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jean-Luke" href="/user/show/9257436-jean-luke">Jean-Luke</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780307744425" href="/book/show/13052956-the-buddha-in-the-attic">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2862055737" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3759045097944393051">(First [re]read of 2021, and I&apos;m still as mesmerized as the first time around. Forever a favorite.)<br/><br/>All of us are readers. Some of us made the journey to the library, by walking, by bicycling, by bus, and others clicked a button on a screen. Several of us paid good money for the book, hoping, praying, that it wouldn&apos;t be a disappointment. Most could afford it, but some could not, and what a tragedy that would be!<br/><br/>Some of us heard good things, others picked it up on a whim. <i>Pretty cover</i> ran through</span>
  <span id="freeText3759045097944393051" style="display:none">(First [re]read of 2021, and I'm still as mesmerized as the first time around. Forever a favorite.)<br /><br />All of us are readers. Some of us made the journey to the library, by walking, by bicycling, by bus, and others clicked a button on a screen. Several of us paid good money for the book, hoping, praying, that it wouldn't be a disappointment. Most could afford it, but some could not, and what a tragedy that would be!<br /><br />Some of us heard good things, others picked it up on a whim. <i>Pretty cover</i> ran through some of our heads. In Canada, Austria, Japan. Kyoto, Oakland--the very places mentioned in the book. Some of us loved the book, others liked it well enough. Several couldn't stand the style and may not even have finished reading it. Others finished it simply for the satisfaction of leaving a negative review, but they are certainly the exception.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3759045097944393051" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


