        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2724062491" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13433663126202866492">Between the wars Japanese mail order brides are shipped over the Pacific to marry established Japanese migrants. They experience a variety of outcomes but most create a life for themselves and their families. Then Pearl Harbour happens and the Japanese expats become the enemy within, to be rounded up and interned.<br/><br/>Told in a very effective style featuring multiple short narratives, it is a real page turner.<br/><br/>I really enjoyed this book.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


